					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Remoras live around some of the scariest predators of the sea! They attach on to them using their special suction plate head. In return, the host animal benefits as the remora may feed on parasites that have also attached to the host. The remora benefits from extra protection and free food from the leftovers of it's host's meals.
						</text>
